cs.SC, cs.CG, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with algorithms for computing volumes of semi-algebraic sets using symbolic methods such as Picard-Fuchs differential equations and rational integrals.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also likely as the paper deals with computing volumes of geometric objects (semi-algebraic sets) using algorithms.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is relevant as the paper uses high-precision numerical integration of differential equations.
- cs.DS (Dynamical Systems) is relevant as the paper uses properties of critical points, which are often studied in dynamical systems.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the relationship between volumes of semi-algebraic sets and periods of rational integrals, which can be relevant in control theory.
